reviewText:
Genre: Action/Stealth/Adventure game.

The good:

Optimization;
Graphics;
Voice Acting;
Soundtrack;
Gameplay;
Main Story (50 Missions);
Side Operations; (157 Missions);
Online Base Infiltrations (FOB);
Replayability (S Ranks plus tasks);
Open World Sandbox (With some fauna and flora);
Unlockables (Weapons, Uniforms, etc;
Real Time Weather (Sandstorms, rain, mist);
Drivable Vehicles (Jeeps, tanks, trucks);
Metal Gear Online 3 (Pending);
Private Forces (PF) virtual battles that are scheduled every 3 weeks to win points to spend on rewards. Instead of you invade an FOB the battles are simulated depending on your power" acumulated up to now.

The bad:

Online issues; (It has been fixed)
No full mouse support;
No multiple saves;
Can't shoot the enemy walkie talkie/radio to prevent their communications (like in MGS2 or MGS3);
Can't shoot enemy body parts and incapacitate them (like in MGS2 or MGS3);
Soldiers won't speak while being interrogated (they makes noises and appear subtitles);
Not much interior infiltrations;
Repetitive environment

date:
 Africa and Afghanistan;
Inaccessible areas of the map.

Score: 9/10."
